const stats = { totalProjects: projects.length, completedProjects: projects.filter(p => p.status === 'completed').length, totalUsers: projects.reduce((sum, p) => sum + parseInt(p.metrics.users.replace(/[^0-9]/g, '')), 0), avgRating: (projects.reduce((sum, p) => sum + parseFloat(p.metrics.rating), 0) / projects.length).toFixed(1) };
